Optimization involves an objective funtion which allows you to find the optical solution in a particular problem or situation by locating the best value in the feasible region. 

You would use optimization when you are trying to find out, for example, the the maximum amount of chairs to produce at a furniture store to maximise your profit, without losing money on excess chairs in inventory.

The components of the linear programming are as follows:
-Objective or goal which is the target sell
-changing cells which you can adjust the amount to change the optimal solution
-constraints which are limitations or restrictions.
